      "side": 1,
      "message": "TOCTOU (Time-of-Check to Time-of-Use) Race in start_pty_process Alias Registration\n\nThe alias uniqueness check and the actual registration in self._processes are in two separate lock acquisitions. A second call with the same alias arriving between the two with self._lock blocks would pass the uniqueness check and both calls would register, with the second overwriting the first\u0027s child and log_fh without closing them.\n\nSuggestion fix is to Open the file and spawn the process outside the lock (they\u0027re blocking I/O), then perform a second check-and-set inside the final lock acquisition before writing to the dicts\n\n```\nwith self._lock:\n    if alias in self._processes:  # re-check inside lock\n        child.close(force\u003dTrue)\n        log_fh.close()\n        raise RuntimeError(\n            \"A PTY process with alias \u0027{}\u0027 is already running. \"\n            \"Stop it first with \u0027Stop PTY Process\u0027.\".format(alias)\n        )\n    self._processes[alias] \u003d child\n    self._log_handles[alias] \u003d log_fh\n    self._log_paths[alias] \u003d log_file\n```\n\nPrevents silently leaked file handles and orphaned child processes in concurrent suite execution scenarios.",
      "revId": "408359742cffc5a06a26f16082ed23dea5f06ccd",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
