      "message": "Hardcoded Device-Specific HOST_COMMAND_PROMPT\n\nThis variable embeds a specific device hostname (raspberrypi-4f8b). The SSH test asserts Should Contain ${output} ${HOST_COMMAND_PROMPT} in the Verify Standalone SOL output from DCSCM using SBC over SSH test case, which will always fail on any hardware other than this exact RPI unit.\n\nSuggestion fix is to Make HOST_COMMAND_PROMPT an externally supplied variable with a generic default, or widen the assertion to match a broader pattern:\n\n```\n${HOST_COMMAND_PROMPT}       qualcomm@      # matches any qualcomm@\u003chostname\u003e\n```\n\nHardcoded device identifiers are a portability anti-pattern that will cause immediate failures in CI or on any other EVB+RPI configuration",
