      "side": 1,
      "message": "Either you do it in one place, Test teardown or Suite Teardown for this case thats the first one.. \n\nNext,\n\nThese Terminate Process calls reference handle names (sol_proc, sol_tc06, sol_client1, sol_client2) from Robot Framework\u0027s built-in Process library, but none of the test cases in this suite start processes via Process.Start Process using those handles. All sessions are managed exclusively via the PTY library. These calls are dead code left over from an earlier implementation.\n\nWhat we should do is Remove the four Terminate Process lines from both Suite Teardown Execution and Test Teardown Execution, leaving only Stop All PTY Processes for session cleanup.\n\nDead code adds noise, misleads future maintainers, and could mask a legitimate process leak by absorbing errors silently (Run Keyword And Ignore Error).",
